    "body": "### Expected\r\nI would expect when I make a spelling mistake, the app will help me auto-correct it, or at least indicate a spelling error. \r\n\r\n### Observed\r\nNothing happens when I make a spelling mistake on the notes, even though spell check is enabled on my mobile device settings.\r\n\r\n### Reproduced\r\n**Note:** The issue was originally reported in 4110365-zen but I'm able to replicate this on my device.\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n1. Make sure spelling correction is enabled on your device.\r\n2. Open Simplenote app\r\n3. Create a new note\r\n4. Type a wrong word, e.g. contry\r\n5. See that the app does nothing with the wrong word.\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35628116/125277705-11a6e980-e312-11eb-8f27-de22f922f062.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\nDevice Make: Samsung\r\nDevice Model: Galaxy S9+ \r\nAndroid Version: 10.0.0\r\nSimplenote Version: 2.18\r\n",
